@lsm5 I'm curious why this is needed.  My understanding is `GO111MODULE=off` is only necessary when using really, really, old versions of golang, no?

---

CI test-job wise, this sounds like something ripe for inclusion in `alt_build_task`.  This is a kind of catch-all for "Confirm building works in *" scenarios.  To add something new, just toss in a new matrix item to that task with a distinct `$ALT_NAME` value.  Then pick that up with a [new entry in the runner script case block.](https://github.com/containers/podman/blob/b6b0b6e8bd0f8c75fe9411f722a43f9305c6137a/contrib/cirrus/runner.sh#L208-L250)
